commit_message:
fix #28: correct widths for wide columns

Add test_table_auto_width() that checks for a table to behave the same
way if one column is wider than its equal share of max_width compared
to when all columns stay below that, assuming max_width is large enough
to accomodate the complete table.

Adjust auto_calculate_width() to keep the actual width if it's smaller
than the new one with adjusted share. This fixes issue #28 and passes
the new test.

I'm not sure why the flagging by equally shared width is used, so I
left it in. This may be improvable with more insight into what the
width adjustment is meant to solve.

commit_message:
rewrite for v1.0.0

Make several API changes which were pending for a long time.
Most of the older APIs have been deprecated to allow for better things in the future.
One important advantage is that now Row headers are available.
Foundation for merging cells has been added which is currently planned to be used but not limited to spanning cells support.

* Fixes #57 (ANSI regex issue with Blessings)
* Fixes #65 (separate header alignment)
* Progress on #74 . (cell spanning) (targeted for v1.1.0)
* Fixes #89 , #27 , #15 (A better interface for auto vs manual width)
* Fixes #90 (Row headers)
